File: internal/client/providers/sqlite/embed.go
Package: sqlite
Purpose: Embeds migration SQL files from migrations/*.sql into binary via go:embed directive. Provides migrationsFS embed.FS for goose migrations.

File: internal/client/providers/sqlite/sqlite.go
Package: sqlite
Purpose: Opens, creates, validates, and hardens client SQLite database file. Imports: modernc.org/sqlite.

Errors: ErrEmptyPath, ErrParentDirNotDirectory, ErrParentDirInsecurePermissions, ErrDatabaseFileNotRegular, ErrDatabaseFileInsecurePermissions.

Functions:
func Open(path string) (*sql.DB, error). Trims path, ensures parent dir exists mode 700, ensures DB file exists mode 600, validates existing file permissions, opens sqlite, pings, configures pragmas. Effects: may create parent dir mode 700 and DB file mode 600. Errors: ErrEmptyPath, ensureParentDir errors, ensureDatabaseFile errors, validateDatabaseFile errors, open/ping/pragma errors. Cleanup Required: caller closes returned DB.
func ensureParentDir(dir string) error. Creates dir mode 700 if missing, validates existing dir, rejects non-directories, validates permissions.
func ensureDatabaseFile(path string) (bool, error). Returns true if existing regular file, creates missing file with O_RDWR|O_CREATE|O_EXCL mode 600, rejects non-regular paths.
func validateDatabaseFile(path string) error. Requires regular file and platform-specific secure permissions.
func configureSQLite(db *sql.DB) error. Sets MaxOpenConns=1, enables foreign_keys, sets busy_timeout=5000ms, requires journal_mode WAL. Errors: pragma failures, error if WAL not returned.

Concurrency and Thread Safety: DB constrained to single open connection via MaxOpenConns=1.
Security Constraints: Enforces 0700 parent directories and 0600 DB files on Unix. Foreign keys enabled, WAL mode for concurrency.
Warnings: Windows permission validation incomplete. ensureDatabaseFile creates file mode 600 but parent dir permissions may allow other access if parent insecure. MaxOpenConns=1 limits concurrency but prevents lock conflicts.


File: internal/client/providers/sqlite/errors.go
Package: sqlite
Purpose: Declares structural error flags indicating insecure filesystem posture states.
Globals: ErrParentDirInsecurePermissions, ErrDatabaseFileInsecurePermissions.

File: internal/client/providers/sqlite/perms_unix.go
Package: sqlite
Build: unix
Purpose: Assures standard POSIX octal file permission compliance rules hold over localized rest storage.
Functions:
func validateDirPermissions(path string, info os.FileInfo) error. Verifies mode matches exactly 0700. Errors: ErrParentDirInsecurePermissions.
func validateFilePermissions(path string, info os.FileInfo) error. Verifies mode matches exactly 0600. Errors: ErrDatabaseFileInsecurePermissions.

File: internal/client/providers/sqlite/perms_windows.go
Package: sqlite
Build: windows
Purpose: Grants absolute encryption container protection at rest on Windows by manipulating native kernel DACL blocks.
Functions:
func validateDirPermissions(path string, info os.FileInfo) error. Targets container directory namespaces.
func validateFilePermissions(path string, info os.FileInfo) error. Targets physical database files.
func aclProtectCurrentURLExclusive(path string) error. Extracts executing process user SIDs, constructs explicit access matrices, and strips parent folder inheritance via PROTECTED_DACL_SECURITY_INFORMATION to lock contents to the active owner.

File: internal/client/providers/sqlite/migrate.go
Package: sqlite
Purpose: Safely manages embedded schema installation rules for local SQLite databases.
Globals: ErrNilDatabase.
Functions:
func Migrate(db *sql.DB) error. Execution finalizer. Implements a mandatory entryguard to intercept null connection wrappers, sets up goose engine environments, and rolls schema updates. Errors: ErrNilDatabase, dial, or syntax execution faults.
Security Constraints: Terminates processing immediately on uninitialized database handlers to prevent runtime environment segmentation violations.
